  "description": "[h1]Real-World LoL Rosters 2026[/h1]\n\nPlay Teamfight Manager 2 with actual esports teams and pro players inspired by https://steamcommunity.com/id/Carvarx aka /u/CarvarX on Reddit\n\n[h2]Features[/h2]\n[list]\n[*] 120 real teams - LCK, LPL, LEC, LCS, CBLOL, and more\n[*] 1,197 pro players with real in-game names\n[*] Stats derived from Oracle's Elixir competitive data\n[*] Custom team logos for major organizations\n[/list]\n\n[h2]Included Teams[/h2]\nGen.G, T1, Hanwha Life, Bilibili Gaming, JD Gaming, Top Esports, G2 Esports, Fnatic, Cloud9, Team Liquid, LOUD, paiN Gaming, and 108 more!\n\n[h2]Installation[/h2]\n1. Subscribe to this mod\n2. Copy the .tfm2db file to: %APPDATA%\\TeamSamoyed\\TeamfightManager2\\data\\\n3. Rename to custom_database.tfm2db\n4. Create empty file: custom_db_enabled.flag\n5. Restart game\n\n[h2]Data Source[/h2]\nPlayer stats derived from [url=https://oracleselixir.com/]Oracle's Elixir[/url] 2026 Spring split data.\n\n[h2]Notes[/h2]\n[list]\n[*] Data from 2026 Spring - latest transfers may not be included\n[*] Stats are approximations of real competitive performance\n[*] Some hidden fields (ages, potential) could not be modified\n[/list]\n\n[h2]Source Code & Tools[/h2]\nGitHub: [url=https://github.com/eminyilmazz/tfm2-real-teams-and-rosters]eminyilmazz/tfm2-real-teams-and-rosters[/url]\n\nIncludes Go tools to create your own roster mods\n\n[h2]AI Assistance Disclosure[/h2]\nThis project was developed with assistance from generative AI. The AI helped with:\n\n- Reverse-engineering the tfm2db binary format\n- Writing the Go unpacking/repacking tools\n- Generating stat conversion formulas\n- Debugging file corruption issues\n- Writing GitHub documentation\n\n[i]Not affiliated with Team Samoyed or Riot Games. Fan project.[/i]"
}